{
  "stem": "19210.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were free, they were on the way to Eretz Israel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were Jewish-- many times, you could see the Jewish teachers, as well, dancing the oro, the horo, and, and, and singing some Hebrew songs.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because among some of these children, and particularly I would say Polish Jewish children, they had many, many Hebrew training in Poland even before they left, actually.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so they knew more Hebrew than anybody else that I remember already.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So there was many happy times aboard the ship.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It took-- took us about three or four days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was only a scary moment-- not a moment, I should say perhaps longer than a moment.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We left Cadiz and maybe a day later, we received over the loudspeakers orders from the-- the captain of the not to panic because there was German submarine action in the Mediterranean at the time.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we saw a submarine, we saw a German submarine which surfaced.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And because of it, the ship had to make a long detour.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because as you well know, the-- the Germans, they dominated pretty much for a given period of time the Mediterranean seas with their submarines.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So that was pretty scary because at the time, the-- many of the refugees, they couldn't accept that idea that they-- they got out of the-- Germany, et cetera, alive or Poland or et cetera and to finish this way in the middle of the ocean, it was not quite acceptable.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so there was discussions about it later on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the next scare that we had was there was a very rough sea, and the was really waving from side to side.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Long waves would come to the ship and sweep the ship.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
